					<description><![CDATA[I should probably mention this, considering the con starts Friday.   I had too much stuff to do to get ready for the con, and I plum forgot to tell anyone I was going.  Whoops! Anyway, yes!  Twist will be making an appearance at this year&#8217;s Clockwork Alchemy con, in San Jose, California, from May [&#8230;]]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.clockworkalchemy.com/" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-medium wp-image-353 alignleft" src="http://192.185.17.126/~cwtwist/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/untitled.jpg?w=259" alt="Untitled" width="259" height="300" srcset="http://clockworktwist.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/untitled.jpg 777w, http://clockworktwist.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/untitled-259x300.jpg 259w" sizes="(max-width: 259px) 100vw, 259px" /></a>I should probably mention this, considering the con starts Friday.   I had too much stuff to do to get ready for the con, and I plum forgot to tell anyone I was going.  Whoops!</p>
<p>Anyway, yes!  Twist will be making an appearance at this year&#8217;s Clockwork Alchemy con, in San Jose, California, from May 23rd through 26th.  Just like last year, I&#8217;ll be signing books at the table, and selling swag.  I&#8217;ll have the first 2 books on sale, and even some new shiny buttons.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignright  wp-image-2279" src="http://192.185.17.126/~cwtwist/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/20140519_123740.jpg" alt="20140519_123740" width="252" height="189" srcset="http://clockworktwist.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/20140519_123740.jpg 3264w, http://clockworktwist.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/20140519_123740-300x225.jpg 300w, http://clockworktwist.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/20140519_123740-1024x768.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 252px) 100vw, 252px" />If you&#8217;re in the San Jose area and like a bit of steampunk, come in for the day!  There&#8217;ll be musical and special guests, lots of things to buy with gears glued on, weirdos&#8211;erm&#8230;  I mean, wonderfully attired individuals, and a library of all things steampunk with loads of authors and book signings!</p>
<p>Of course, you know, I won&#8217;t get to see much of the con myself, as I&#8217;ll be mostly at my author table.  So, please do come and say hi!  It would be lovely to chat with you.  And if you come in costume, I&#8217;ll be taking as many pictures as I can and posting them all right here on the blog!  I had a lovely time meeting a lot of you last year, and I&#8217;m looking forward to seeing you again.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
