										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.clockworkalchemy.com/" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-medium wp-image-353 alignleft" alt="Untitled" src="http://192.185.17.126/~cwtwist/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/untitled.jpg?w=259" width="259" height="300" srcset="http://clockworktwist.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/untitled.jpg 777w, http://clockworktwist.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/untitled-259x300.jpg 259w" sizes="(max-width: 259px) 100vw, 259px" /></a></p>
<p>It&#8217;s official now.  After much deliberation and form-filling, Twist&#8217;s radiant, erudite (and ever so humble) author will be presenting at this year&#8217;s Clockwork Alchemy steampunk convention in San Jose, Ca, May 24th &#8211; 27th!</p>
<p>If you&#8217;re in the San Jose area and like a bit of steampunk, come in for the day!  There&#8217;ll be musical and special guests, lots of things to buy with gears glued on, weirdos&#8211;erm&#8230;  I mean, wonderfully attired individuals, and a library of all things steampunk with loads of authors and book signings!</p>
<p>I&#8217;ll be there as well, signing books and selling swag.  I also want to post lots of photos with my gorgeous readers on this site, so if you come to the con be sure to look for me in the author section and say hi!  I hope to see you there.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
